[Case 13 Round 3 Step 11] CANDIDATE: {"response": {"action": "solve", "solve": {"working_diagnosis": "Multiple myeloma (IgA kappa) in very good partial remission with treatment-related multi-organ toxicity: chemotherapy-induced myelosuppression (anemia, neutropenia, thrombocytopenia), drug-induced cholestatic hepatotoxicity, and cardiac strain (NT-proBNP elevation) secondary to atrial fibrillation and volume overload. No evidence of AL amyloidosis. Patient is a transplant-eligible candidate requiring therapy modification and intensive supportive care.", "differentials": ["Chemotherapy-induced myelodysplastic syndrome (rule out with cytogenetics on marrow)", "Heparin-induced thrombocytopenia (unlikely, on apixaban)", "Congestive heart failure exacerbation from volume overload", "Progressive myeloma with plasma cell leukemia (ruled out by marrow showing 5% plasma cells)"], "treatment_plan": [{"action": "IMMEDIATE ANTI-MYELOMA THERAPY MODIFICATION", "intention": "therapeutic", "priority": 1}, {"action": "Given cytopenias and organ toxicities while in VGPR, reduce current IMiD/proteasome inhibitor dose by 50% rather than hold therapy. If on bortezomib-based regimen, switch to ixazomib 3 mg weekly (oral, less neuropathy). If on lenalidomide, switch to pomalidomide 2 mg daily (less hepatotoxic). Maintain dexamethasone at lowest effective dose (20 mg weekly or less)", "intention": "therapeutic", "priority": 1}, {"action": "INFECTIOUS RISK MITIGATION", "intention": "therapeutic", "priority": 1}, {"action": "Urgent oral surgery/dental consultation within 72 hours for source control; start prophylactic amoxicillin-clavulanate 500/125 mg TID for 10 days pre- and post-procedure. Add antifungal prophylaxis with fluconazole 100 mg daily during neutropenia. Hold apixaban 24h pre-procedure per cardiology guidance", "intention": "therapeutic", "priority": 1}, {"action": "HEMATOPOIETIC SUPPORT", "intention": "supportive", "priority": 1}, {"action": "Initiate filgrastim 300 mcg SC 3x/week until ANC >1.5 \u00d7 10\u2079/L, then 300 mcg weekly maintenance. For anemia: check iron studies, ferritin, B12; give IV iron 1000 mg if ferritin <100 or TSAT <20%. Start darbepoetin alfa 500 mcg every 3 weeks targeting Hb 10-11 g/dL. Platelet support: hold anti-platelet agents; if Plt <50, consider thrombopoietin receptor agonist", "intention": "supportive", "priority": 1}, {"action": "CARDIAC OPTIMIZATION", "intention": "therapeutic", "priority": 2}, {"action": "Increase torasemide to 10 mg daily for volume management. Target BP <140/90 with ramipril up to 10 mg daily. Bisoprolol uptitration to 5 mg BID for rate control in AF. Repeat NT-proBNP in 2 weeks; if >1500 pg/mL or clinical deterioration, add mineralocorticoid receptor antagonist (spironolactone 25 mg daily)", "intention": "therapeutic", "priority": 2}, {"action": "HEPATIC TOXICITY MANAGEMENT", "intention": "supportive", "priority": 2}, {"action": "Hold non-essential hepatotoxins: discontinue pantoprazole (switch to famotidine 20 mg BID). Check HBV/HCV serologies and CMV/EBV viral loads. Obtain abdominal Doppler ultrasound to evaluate hepatic blood flow. If LFTs worsen (>3x ULN), hold anti-myeloma therapy until recovery to <2x ULN, then restart at 50% dose", "intention": "supportive", "priority": 2}, {"action": "SYMPTOM CONTROL & NUTRITION", "intention": "supportive", "priority": 3}, {"action": "For dysgeusia: zinc sulfate 220 mg daily, magic mouthwash (lidocaine/diphenhydramine/Maalox) before meals, aggressive oral hygiene with chlorhexidine, and nutritional shakes (Ensure/Boost). For fatigue: rule out hypothyroidism (TSH), testosterone deficiency, and depression escalation (increase sertraline to 150 mg if needed)", "intention": "supportive", "priority": 3}, {"action": "LONG-TERM DISEASE STRATEGY", "intention": "therapeutic", "priority": 1}, {"action": "Patient remains transplant-eligible (age 67, VGPR, adequate organ function despite toxicities). Plan for ASCT after 2-4 more cycles of dose-reduced